02:27:06.000 --> 02:27:08.000 align:middle line:-2
Karan?
- No one has arrived yet.

02:27:45.280 --> 02:27:46.520 align:middle line:-1
Yes.

02:27:52.560 --> 02:27:53.640 align:middle line:-2
Was there a girl
called Khushi here?

02:27:53.720 --> 02:27:55.080 align:middle line:-1
There's no one.

02:27:58.640 --> 02:27:59.920 align:middle line:-1
Thank you.

02:28:27.560 --> 02:28:30.600 align:middle line:-2
Maybe he has gone to
Mumbai Central to meet me.

02:28:31.520 --> 02:28:33.600 align:middle line:-2
Maybe she has gone
to VT Station to meet me.

02:28:33.680 --> 02:28:34.880 align:middle line:-1
And what if he hasn't?

02:28:35.440 --> 02:28:36.600 align:middle line:-1
Now?

02:28:41.320 --> 02:28:42.440 align:middle line:-1
Okay.

02:28:42.800 --> 02:28:44.000 align:middle line:-1
Okay.

02:28:47.240 --> 02:28:51.560 align:middle line:-2
A girl called Khushi will come
here. Please give her this letter.

02:28:51.680 --> 02:28:52.600 align:middle line:-1
Okay.

02:28:54.040 --> 02:28:57.560 align:middle line:-2
A boy called Karan will come here.
Please give him this.

02:28:57.640 --> 02:28:58.440 align:middle line:-1
Okay.

02:30:38.400 --> 02:30:39.320 align:middle line:-1
Karan?

02:30:39.400 --> 02:30:40.600 align:middle line:-1
Yes?

02:30:43.960 --> 02:30:45.240 align:middle line:-1
'Dear, Karan.'

02:30:45.440 --> 02:30:47.840 align:middle line:-2
'I wanted to tell you something
for a very long time.'

02:30:48.320 --> 02:30:52.760 align:middle line:-2
'You know what?
I love you, Khushi.'

02:30:54.000 --> 02:30:57.120 align:middle line:-2
'When we were together,
this is what I wanted to say,'

02:30:57.360 --> 02:31:01.040 align:middle line:-2
'but I never could,
I don't know why.'

02:31:01.280 --> 02:31:04.600 align:middle line:-2
'And now that I want to speak,
you are not with me.'

02:31:04.680 --> 02:31:07.600 align:middle line:-2
'We said so much to each
other when we fought,'

02:31:07.720 --> 02:31:11.280 align:middle line:-2
'but we couldn't say one
single word to get together.

02:31:11.960 --> 02:31:14.880 align:middle line:-1
I'm sorry, Khushi.'

02:31:14.960 --> 02:31:18.800 align:middle line:-2
'When I left your hand
after the last handshake,'

02:31:18.880 --> 02:31:21.400 align:middle line:-2
'I felt something strange
stir in my heart.'

02:31:21.520 --> 02:31:26.000 align:middle line:-2
'I don't know what it was.
But I need you, Karan.'

02:31:26.040 --> 02:31:32.280 align:middle line:-2
'I now realise that the fights
we had were all part of our love.'

02:31:33.640 --> 02:31:35.600 align:middle line:-1
'I need you, Khushi.'

02:31:36.640 --> 02:31:40.120 align:middle line:-1
'To love me, to fight with me.'

02:31:47.320 --> 02:31:50.520 align:middle line:-2
You're a lucky girl
to have a father like yours.

02:31:50.600 --> 02:31:52.440 align:middle line:-2
Ever since you agreed
to the wedding,

02:31:52.560 --> 02:31:54.400 align:middle line:-2
all he has done is
to look out for suitors.

02:31:54.520 --> 02:31:58.640 align:middle line:-2
He decided to have you married
the day you returned from the city.

02:31:58.840 --> 02:32:01.880 align:middle line:-2
Everything is ready.
The bridegroom, the garland

02:32:01.960 --> 02:32:05.120 align:middle line:-1
step forward and be garlanded.

02:32:14.400 --> 02:32:18.160 align:middle line:-1
Lali! My dear!

02:32:18.440 --> 02:32:21.080 align:middle line:-1
You're back! Welcome home!

02:32:21.360 --> 02:32:23.880 align:middle line:-2
Go and get ready quickly.
- But dad...

02:32:24.000 --> 02:32:28.320 align:middle line:-2
Just don't worry, my little girl.
The boy I've chosen this time,

02:32:28.400 --> 02:32:31.320 align:middle line:-2
is neither running away
nor leaving behind letters,

02:32:31.400 --> 02:32:34.240 align:middle line:-2
and he's not in love
with another girl either.

02:32:34.320 --> 02:32:36.680 align:middle line:-2
Dad!
- Why are you chanting dad?

02:32:36.760 --> 02:32:38.280 align:middle line:-2
Go and get dressed quickly.
- Hurry up and get ready.

02:32:38.400 --> 02:32:40.960 align:middle line:-2
Just a minute.
- Dad!

02:32:51.920 --> 02:32:54.280 align:middle line:-2
Lali, take a look
at your bridegroom.

02:32:56.080 --> 02:32:57.920 align:middle line:-1
Take a look at him.

02:33:15.360 --> 02:33:18.000 align:middle line:-2
You left this note
for him in the train

02:33:18.400 --> 02:33:20.440 align:middle line:-2
and he turned out
to be faster than you.

02:33:20.680 --> 02:33:25.320 align:middle line:-2
He halted the train and
took a flight to get here.

02:33:25.400 --> 02:33:27.080 align:middle line:-1
He has told me everything.

02:33:27.280 --> 02:33:30.800 align:middle line:-2
Karan's parents will also
be coming here for the wedding.

02:33:30.880 --> 02:33:32.200 align:middle line:-1
Are you happy now?

02:33:32.840 --> 02:33:34.160 align:middle line:-1
Thank you, dad.

02:34:42.280 --> 02:34:48.080 align:middle line:-2
'This is how two hearts
met and accepted each other.'

02:34:49.120 --> 02:34:53.280 align:middle line:-2
'They're celebrating
their ninth anniversary'

02:34:53.560 --> 02:34:57.120 align:middle line:-2
'and they're still fighting.
What is surprising is that'

02:34:57.240 --> 02:35:01.880 align:middle line:-2
'they don't have one or two kids,
they have 17 children in 8 years.'

02:35:02.320 --> 02:35:05.840 align:middle line:-2
'Twins every year. But
how does it still add up to 17?'

02:35:06.280 --> 02:35:10.080 align:middle line:-2
'Confusing, isn't it?
They didn't fight for a year,'

02:35:10.280 --> 02:35:11.640 align:middle line:-1
'and they had triplets.'

02:35:13.680 --> 02:35:19.280 align:middle line:-2
'Khushi's expecting again.
Twins or triplets, I don't know. '

02:35:19.640 --> 02:35:24.640 align:middle line:-2
'I'm just looking
on and praying for them.'

02:35:25.000 --> 02:35:28.280 align:middle line:-2
'May Karan keep giving Khushi
this happiness all her life. '
